---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Kickle — Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy Policy for Kickle: Football Quiz by Ediz Yilmaz."
  legal={true}
>
  <p><a href="/privacy" class="back-link">← Back to Privacy</a></p>

  <h1>Kickle — Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="muted">Effective Date: June 13, 2026</p>

  <p>
    This Privacy Policy applies to <strong>Kickle: Football Quiz</strong> and
    <strong>Kickle: Soccer Quiz &amp; Trivia</strong> (the "Application"), a mobile app
    provided by <strong>Ediz Yilmaz</strong> (the "Service Provider"). The Application is
    provided as a freemium service and is intended for use as is.
  </p>

  <h2>Information the Application collects</h2>
  <p>
    Kickle does not require account registration, an email address, a phone number, or a
    real name. The Application may collect or process the following information:
  </p>
  <ul class="list">
    <li><strong>User ID:</strong> a random app-generated identifier stored on your device and used for leaderboard ranking and purchase entitlement checks.</li>
    <li><strong>Display name:</strong> the short leaderboard name you choose in the Application.</li>
    <li><strong>Approximate location:</strong> your country or region, derived from device locale or by advertising partners, used for regional leaderboards and advertising.</li>
    <li><strong>Gameplay data:</strong> score, accuracy, streak, game mode, app version, premium status, and played timestamp for leaderboard functionality.</li>
    <li><strong>Purchase history and subscription status:</strong> used to provide Kickle Pro features and remove ads for eligible users.</li>
    <li><strong>Advertising data and device identifiers:</strong> collected by advertising partners to show and measure ads, subject to your App Tracking Transparency and consent choices.</li>
    <li><strong>Usage, performance, crash, and diagnostic data:</strong> collected to operate, secure, measure, and improve the Application and advertising services.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How information is used</h2>
  <p>The information above may be used for the following purposes:</p>
  <ul class="list">
    <li>Providing core app functionality, including rounds, scores, streaks, leaderboards, and premium access.</li>
    <li>Processing and restoring in-app purchases and subscriptions.</li>
    <li>Displaying ads and measuring ad performance.</li>
    <li>Managing privacy consent where required by law.</li>
    <li>Improving app reliability, performance, and user experience.</li>
    <li>Preventing abuse of leaderboard and premium systems.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Third-party services</h2>
  <p>
    The Application uses third-party services that may collect information according to
    their own privacy policies:
  </p>
  <ul class="list">
    <li><a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy">Google Privacy Policy</a> — Google Mobile Ads and Google User Messaging Platform are used for ads, consent management, and ad measurement.</li>
    <li><a href="https://www.revenuecat.com/privacy">RevenueCat Privacy Policy</a> — RevenueCat is used to manage in-app purchases, subscriptions, entitlements, and purchase restoration.</li>
    <li><a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/">Apple Privacy Policy</a> — App Store purchases and platform-level privacy settings are handled by Apple.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Advertising, tracking, and consent</h2>
  <p>
    Kickle may show ads through Google Mobile Ads. On iOS, the Application asks for App
    Tracking Transparency permission before accessing the advertising identifier where
    required. In regions where additional consent is required, Google User Messaging
    Platform may present privacy choices for personalized ads and related processing.
  </p>
  <p>
    You can change tracking permissions at any time in iOS Settings → Privacy &amp; Security
    → Tracking. Users in applicable regions may also be shown Google privacy choices in
    the Application.
  </p>

  <h2>In-app purchases</h2>
  <p>
    Kickle offers optional in-app purchases and subscriptions, including Kickle Pro.
    Purchase transactions are processed by Apple, and subscription status is managed with
    RevenueCat. The Service Provider does not receive your payment card details.
  </p>

  <h2>Data sharing</h2>
  <p>
    Information may be shared with service providers only as needed to operate the
    Application, including leaderboard hosting, advertising, consent management, purchase
    management, diagnostics, and fraud prevention. The Service Provider does not sell your
    personal information.
  </p>

  <h2>Data retention</h2>
  <p>
    Leaderboard and premium entitlement records may be retained while needed to provide
    the Application, maintain score history, prevent abuse, and support purchase-related
    features. Diagnostic and advertising data is retained according to the policies of the
    relevant third-party providers. You may request deletion of data associated with your
    app-generated user ID by contacting the Service Provider.
  </p>

  <h2>Your choices and rights</h2>
  <ul class="list">
    <li>You can stop all future collection by uninstalling the Application.</li>
    <li>You can reset or limit advertising tracking using iOS privacy settings.</li>
    <li>You can request access, correction, or deletion of data associated with your app-generated user ID.</li>
    <li>If you are in the EEA, UK, Switzerland, or another region with privacy rights, you may also have the right to object to or restrict certain processing and to lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>
    The Application is not directed to children under 13, and the Service Provider does not
    knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe a child
    has provided personal information through the Application, please contact the Service
    Provider so the information can be deleted.
  </p>

  <h2>Security</h2>
  <p>
    The Service Provider uses reasonable technical and organizational safeguards to protect
    information processed by the Application. No method of transmission or storage is
    completely secure, so absolute security cannot be guaranteed.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Changes will be posted on this
    page with a new effective date. Continued use of the Application after changes are
    posted means you accept the updated policy.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    For privacy questions or requests, contact:
    <a href="mailto:edizyilmaz@icloud.com">edizyilmaz@icloud.com</a>
  </p>
</Layout>
